Head
(
Fig. 16
). Epicranial notch moderately flat, half length of epicranial suture. P1 arises closer to AF2 than A1. Five stemmata present and evenly distributed in an anteriodorsally arch. Stems 4–5 just below 3. Mandible with five cusps which become smaller mesally (
Fig. 17
). Clypeus triangular (
Fig. 18
). Labrum with six pairs of dorsal setae, all moderately long (
Fig. 19
), venter of labrum with three pairs of epipharyngal setae (
Fig. 20
, two mesal setae markedly longer than lateral seta). Labial palpus with a very elongated basal segment, with 2/3 the length of spinneret mesal segment greatly reduced, only one tenth the length of segment 1, apical amount of segment 2 long, ~ twice the length of segment 2. Spinneret long and slender, gradually tapering to a narrow, simple point.
